3	//! Unit D of the relicensing effort. Every observable string in this crate was
4	//! derived from black-box probing of the compiled binary (see
5	//! `workspace/BEHAVIOR.md` and `workspace/QUERIES.log`); exact output strings
6	//! (help pages, banners, error texts) are stored as observed-output fixtures and
7	//! treated as opaque compatibility content. The parsing architecture, flag-table
